Name.label: Syndactyly-camptodactyly and clinodactyly of fifth fingers-bifid toes syndrome
Syndrome with limb duplication, polydactyly, syndactyly, and/or hyperphalangy

TextSection.Contents: A rare, genetic, congenital limb malformation syndrome characterized by a unique combination of bilateral, symmetrical camptodactyly and clinodactyly of 5th fingers, mesoaxial camptodactyly of toes, and ulnar deviation of 3rd fingers. Additional variable manifestations include bifid toes and severe syndactyly, or synpolydactyly, involving all digits of hands and feet.

Name.label: E (exact mapping (the terms and the concepts are equivalent))
